<TITLE> Body of ATN Bangla cameraman recovered </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)  Police on Sunday recovered the body of a cameraman employed by private television channel ATN Bangla near an embankment along the river Turag, Tongi. Thirty three year old Shafiqul Islam Mithu, 33, lived in the capital's Dakkhin Khan area. Police recovered the body at around 10am from the road near Rustompur embankment. Mithu's brother identified the body, a senior journalist of ATN Bangla said. Turag police chief Salauddin told bdnews24.com that there were some marks of wounds on his neck and hands. Mithu has been missing since he left the ATN Bangla office on his way to his home at around midnight on Saturday, he said. The police officer suspected that he had been strangled. A general diary was filed with the Dakkhin Khan police Saturday night as he did not return home. bdn
